Workflow 1: Blood Donation and Inventory Management
Actors Involved

Donor

Staff

System

Database

Workflow Description

Donor arrives at the blood bank.

Staff collects donor details and health information.

Decision Point: Check donor eligibility.

If not eligible, the process stops and donor is informed.

If eligible, the process continues.

Blood donation is performed.

Parallel Activities Begin:

Blood sample testing.

Donation details entry into the system.

After testing:

If blood is safe, it is approved for storage.

If blood is unsafe, it is discarded.

Approved blood units are added to inventory.

Inventory details are updated in the database.

Confirmation is generated.

Workflow ends.

Decision Points

Donor eligibility check

Blood safety test result

Parallel Activities

Medical testing

System data entry

Workflow 2: Blood Request and Allocation Process
Actors Involved

Hospital / Patient

System

Inventory

Admin / Staff

Workflow Description

Hospital/Patient submits blood request.

System receives and validates request.

Decision Point: Check blood availability.

If available, proceed to allocation.

If not available, notify requester and stop.

Parallel Activities Begin (if available):

Inventory stock update.

Request approval and documentation.

Blood unit is allocated.

Notification is sent to hospital.

Request details are stored in database.

Workflow ends.

Decision Points

Blood availability

Request approval

Parallel Activities

Inventory update

Notification generation

Workflow 3: Emergency Blood Request Handling
Actors Involved

Emergency Staff

System

Inventory

Admin

Workflow Description

Emergency request is raised.

System marks request as high priority.

Decision Point: Immediate stock availability.

If available, allocate blood immediately.

If not available, trigger donor search.

Parallel Activities Begin:

Notify nearby donors.

Alert blood bank staff.

Donor response is monitored.

Blood is collected and tested.

Inventory is updated.

Emergency request is fulfilled.

Workflow ends.

Decision Points

Stock availability

Donor response

Parallel Activities

Donor notifications

Staff alerts
